did.abstract: These records mostly include the photographs and negatives taken by Rice News photographers, as well as digital image files and copies of individual newspapers.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Rice News, published for Rice faculty and staff, began in the summer of 1991. It was produced on a weekly basis starting that fall, and continued until 2007. In April of 2007, Rice News ended its print version and transitioned into an online version to provide web-based, real-time information for its audience.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents Note
scopecontent.p: These records mostly include the photographs and negatives taken by Rice News photographers, as well as digital image files and copies of individual newspapers.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This material is open for research. Stored offsite at the Library Service Center and require 24-hour notice for retrieval. Please contact the Woodson Research Center at 713-348-2586 or woodson@rice.edu for more information.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Permission to publish from this material must be obtained from the Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library, Rice University.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Materials were donated by Rice News. We also received digital images covering the issues from May 1996-July 1997. Because some or all of the images were low quality, were not owned by Rice, and/or corresponded to photographs and negatives in the physical files, we did not keep the digital images.

prefercite.p: Rice News photo files, 1995-2006, UA 357, Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library, Rice University
